In a medium to large codebase, many-a-time, you might notice code that shouldn&rsquo;t be in some class/method by design but is necessary. This can be anything from simple logging to transaction handling. As the codebase scales, this keeps adding up to a point where the code becomes laborious to manage.
Aspect-Oriented Programming provides a way to modularize these kinds of cross-cutting concerns with Aspects. Here is a basic example,
@Aspect class LoggingAspect { // Aspect Logger LOGGER = Logger.
